@Sentry87
actually i think you aren't seeing it correctly... i'm almost positive that the mission files are all installed with the game it's just the game always tries to connect to the server at the start of a mission to receive some sort of confirmation. 

if someone had the legit game though i don't think it would be too hard to crack, i'm no expert but i do understand a few things about games and how they work. i think it would be possible to have a program running to listen in on what the ubi server sends the client when you start the mission, copy all said information (hopefully it's relatively the same for all missions) and create crack that tricks the game into looking at the copied info instead of the info from the ubi server. again i'm no expert tho, and i'm not saying it would be easy.

@Bob_Speed you are correct, a listener that monitors the port Ubisoft uses to authenticate the game content would tell us exactly what is needed each time it connects.

Personally, I don't mind waiting for the crack. I really appreciate all the hard work that goes in to letting us play game for free, so I'll wait.

Let it go to show that we say "Fuck you Ubisoft! And your little DRM too!"

